The paper deals with the problem of frequent itemset mining using crowdsourcing, which involves human knowledge and interaction. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. However, the paper also involves computational complexity analysis and algorithms, which are common in Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Databases (cs.DB), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories. Therefore, these sub-categories are also likely candidates.
